webpackJsonp([20919793844349],{1270:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>I like to spend the weekends figuring out neat tricks, learning new skills, and creating cool projects. Yes, I have no life. So, I stumbled on this recut of Mary Poppins as a horror film several years ago and I loved it. Itâ€™s really good and funny, too.</p>\n<p><div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.49999999999999%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2T5_0AGdFic?rel=0" class="embedVideoIframe" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n      <style>\n        .embedVideoIframe {\n          border: 0\n        }\n      </style>\n          </div>\n          </div></p>\n<p>And, much more recently, I stumbled upon this great tutorial on <a href="http://tympanus.net/codrops/2013/04/30/text-opening-sequence-with-css-animations/" title="Text Opening Sequence">creating an opening title sequence using CSS animations from CodeDrops.</a> I bookmarked it and forgot about it. But when I rediscovered it, I really wanted to do something with it. So I did! I created a trailer using the CSS animations, based on the Scary Mary video (plus I created a GIF from <a href="https://archive.org/details/MoonAndCloudsTimeLapse2" title="Moon and Clouds Timelapse">this Moon and Clouds timelapse</a> and added music: <a href="http://incompetech.com/music/royalty-free/index.html?isrc=USUAN1100574" title="Incomptech Royalty Free Music">Awkward Meeting from Kevin McLeod</a>)</p>\n<figure>\n  <a href="http://www.knanthony.com/showcase/opening-sequence/index.html" target="blank">\n    \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 810px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 55.779674166020165%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;" alt="Scary Mary Opening Sequence" title="" src="/static/scary-mary-fd3870f90fa1d49e1e41491361dda0db-1626e.png" srcset="/static/scary-mary-fd3870f90fa1d49e1e41491361dda0db-076ec.png 203w,\n/static/scary-mary-fd3870f90fa1d49e1e41491361dda0db-7ae34.png 405w,\n/static/scary-mary-fd3870f90fa1d49e1e41491361dda0db-1626e.png 810w,\n/static/scary-mary-fd3870f90fa1d49e1e41491361dda0db-9af38.png 1215w,\n/static/scary-mary-fd3870f90fa1d49e1e41491361dda0db-cfeef.png 1289w" sizes="(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n  <figcaption>Check out the final trailer here.</figcaption>\n</figure>',frontmatter:{date:"September 26, 2014",path:"/blog/weekend-project-opening-titles",title:"Weekend Project: Opening Title Sequence",tags:["animation","css","opening","title sequence"],categories:["Design","Weekend Project"],featured:{childImageSharp:{sizes:{base64:"data:image/png;base64,",aspectRatio:1.768172888015717,src:"/static/logoColor-c92143fb3723fcd5f12c0d0502759756-81d39.png",srcSet:"/static/logoColor-c92143fb3723fcd5f12c0d0502759756-9a8d1.png 203w,\n/static/logoColor-c92143fb3723fcd5f12c0d0502759756-c53f9.png 405w,\n/static/logoColor-c92143fb3723fcd5f12c0d0502759756-81d39.png 810w,\n/static/logoColor-c92143fb3723fcd5f12c0d0502759756-e81a9.png 900w",sizes:"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px"}}}}}},pathContext:{}}}});
